            <div type="edition" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="grc" resp="#martaf #AA">
                <ab>
                    <lb n="0"/><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"><desc>name of deceased</desc></gap>
                    <lb n="1"/><w>ἐτελεύτη<supplied reason="lost">σε</supplied></w>
                    <lb n="2"/><w>τῇ</w> <w><expan><abbr>πρ</abbr><ex>ὸ</ex></expan></w> <num value="19">ιθ</num> <w><expan><abbr>Καλα<lb n="3" break="no"/>νδ</abbr><ex>ῶν</ex></expan></w> <w>Ἰανουαρί<lb n="4" break="no"/>ων</w>
                </ab>
            </div>
            <div type="apparatus" resp="#martaf">
                <listApp>
                    <app><note>Text based on photograph</note></app>
                    <app loc="line 1"><note>Kirchhoff, Kaibel: ἐτελεύτη[σε]ν (Kaibel: vel ἐτελεύτ[α]); Korhonen: ἐτελεύτη[σε]</note></app>
                </listApp>
            </div>
            <div type="translation" xml:lang="en" resp="#martaf #AA">
                <p>... died 19 days before the Kalends of January.</p>
            </div>
            <div type="translation" xml:lang="it" resp="#martaf">
                <p>... morì 19 giorni prima delle Calende di gennaio.</p>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary" resp="#martaf">
                <p>This epitaph, already recognised as Christian by Kirchhoff, has a formula fairly attested in Catania without the expression <foreign xml:lang="grc">ἐνθάδε κεῖται</foreign> and with only the name of the deceased followed by the date of death (expressed with the aorist of <foreign xml:lang="grc">τελευτάω</foreign>) and occasionally the age (but not in this case): e.g. IG 14.551 = <ref target="http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic001370">ISic001370</ref>.</p>
            </div>
